discrepancies.canonical_value: Signal characteristics. This message is to be used as a basic spectrum analyzer, where it displays one spectrum for each of the receiver's existing RF paths. The center frequency at each bin, assuming a zero-based bin count, can be computed as f(i) = center + span * (i - 127) / 256.
discrepancies.pdf_value: This message gives information for comparative analysis rather than absolute and precise spectrum overview. Users should not expect highly accurate spectrum amplitude. Note that the PGA gain is not included in the spectrum data but is available as a separate field. Neither the spectrum, nor the PGA gain considers the internal fixed LNA gain or an external third-party LNA. The center frequency at each bin, assuming a zero-based bin count, can be computed as f(i) = center + span * (i - 127) / 256
